init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president's apology is interrupted by a breaking news alert.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Chinese have invaded the Philippines.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president goes on TV again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president goes to bed, but he can't sleep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "This is the President of the United States," the President says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry," says the President, "I'm not trying to order anything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We're out of shrimp toast," says the voice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry," says the President, "I didn't mean to order those.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You can't order those," says the voice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "No," says the President, "I don't want them."
